<frame name="FR_Commitment.to_do" ID="10089" xsi:schemaLocation="../schema/frame.xsd" xmlns="http://framenet.icsi.berkeley.edu" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" domains="Verbal_communication">
    <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;A &lt;fen&gt;Speaker&lt;/fen&gt; makes a commitment to an &lt;fen&gt;Addressee&lt;/fen&gt; to to act so that a future  &lt;fen&gt;Eventuality&lt;/fen&gt; will happen. The eventuality may be desirable (as with &lt;ment&gt;promettre&lt;/ment&gt;) or not desirable (as with &lt;ment&gt;menacer&lt;/ment&gt;) to the &lt;fen&gt;Addressee&lt;/fen&gt;.  For some LUs, alternatively an &lt;fen&gt;Entity&lt;/fen&gt; is direct object, and it is understood that the future action is to provide the Addressee with such an Entity. 
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;fex name="Speaker"&gt;You&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;promised&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Addressee"&gt;me&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;fex name="Eventuality"&gt;you'd come to my graduation&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;

&lt;ex&gt;&lt;fex name="Speaker"&gt;Kim&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;undertook&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Eventuality"&gt;to finish the project by June&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    <FE bgColor="FF0000" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="731" cDate="02/07/2001 04:11:59 PST Wed" abbrev="Spkr" name="Speaker" ID="135">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The Speaker is the person who commits him/herself to do something. 
&lt;ex&gt;  &lt;fex name="Speaker"&gt;Jo&lt;/fex&gt; made a &lt;t&gt;promise&lt;/t&gt; to me. &lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;fex name="Speaker"&gt;Jo&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;promised&lt;/t&gt; me she would cook dinner.
&lt;ex&gt; &lt;fex name="Speaker"&gt;Jo's&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;promise&lt;/t&gt; to cook dinner came to nothing. &lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
        <semType name="Sentient" ID="5"/>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="006400" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="731" cDate="02/07/2001 04:11:59 PST Wed" abbrev="Add" name="Addressee" ID="136">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The person to which the commitment is made.
&lt;ex&gt;Kim made a &lt;t&gt;promise&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Addressee"&gt;to me&lt;/fex&gt;. &lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;ex&gt;Kim &lt;t&gt;promised&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Addressee"&gt;me&lt;/fex&gt; that everything would be okay. &lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
        <semType name="Sentient" ID="5"/>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="0000FF" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="731" cDate="02/07/2001 04:11:59 PST Wed" abbrev="Msg" name="Eventuality" ID="137">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;A future state or event that the Speaker will try to make happen. 
&lt;ex&gt;I &lt;t&gt;swear&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Eventuality"&gt;that this will not happen again.&lt;/fex&gt;. &lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;ex&gt; They &lt;t&gt;threatened&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Message"&gt;revenge&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;
 &lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
  <excludesFE name="Entity" ID="141"/>
        <semType name="State_of_affairs" ID="56"/>
    </FE>
